Why am I getting this error when compiling?
Reason: no LC_RPATH's found
This error typically occurs on macOS when the system cannot find the required dynamic libraries. This is a linking issue rather than a code issue.

To fix this, you need to ensure that:

1. You have Rust installed correctly
2. The required system dependencies are installed

For macOS, you'll likely need to install some additional dependencies. Try installing these using Homebrew:

```bash
brew install cmake pkg-config openssl@1.1
```

If you're still getting the error, you might also need to set some environment variables:

```bash
export OPENSSL_DIR=$(brew --prefix openssl@1.1)
export PKG_CONFIG_PATH="/usr/local/opt/openssl@1.1/lib/pkgconfig"
```

If you're using Apple Silicon (M1/M2), the paths might be slightly different:

```bash
export OPENSSL_DIR=$(brew --prefix openssl@1.1)
export PKG_CONFIG_PATH="/opt/homebrew/opt/openssl@1.1/lib/pkgconfig"
```

After setting these up, try cleaning and rebuilding your project:

```bash
cargo clean
cargo build
```

If the issue persists, you might need to check if all the required dependencies for GPUI and your other dependencies are properly installed on your system.
